article.headline: Oakland, Mich. 79, W. Illinois 50
article.story: ROCHESTER, Mich. -- Drew Valentine, Keith Benson and Reggie Hamilton posted double-doubles as Oakland, Mich., whipped Western Illinois 79-50 on Saturday night. Valentine had 17 points and 14 rebounds, Benson had 13 of each and Hamilton scored 10 points with 10 assists for the Golden Grizzlies (11-8, 6-0), who took over sole possession of first place in the Summit League. Will Hudson was Oakland's leading scorer with 18 points. Travis Bader had 15, all on 3-pointers. Benson added five blocks. Kaimarr Price scored a career-high 17 points to lead the Leathernecks (6-9, 1-4). Brandon Smith added a career-best 12. Price scored Western Illinois' first four baskets and put his team ahead 8-7 before the Golden Grizzlies began to roll. Oakland led 42-18 at halftime, then opened the second half with a 9-0 run. The lead peaked at 35 three times late in the game. Oakland has won 14 straight league games.
